RustPythonNode.js <p><code>dema</code> exposes 1 optional output: <code>"ema"</code>. Pass a boolean mask as the third argument — one <code>bool</code> per optional output, in order.</p> <pre><code>use tulip_rs::indicators::dema::indicator;

let close = vec![81.59, 81.06, 82.87, 83.00, 83.61,
                 83.15, 82.84, 83.99, 84.55, 84.36_f64];

// Request the EMA alongside the DEMA
let mask = [true]; // one per optional output
let (outputs, _state) = indicator(&amp;[close.as_slice()], &amp;[5.0], Some(&amp;mask)).unwrap();

let dema = &amp;outputs[0]; // dema (primary)
let ema  = &amp;outputs[1]; // "ema" (optional — requested)
</code></pre> <pre><code>import numpy as np
